channel.title: WTF, server port
channel.description:
Ok, whenever i try and load up ANY server, i get this
Error: Unable to startup listener on 43594 - port already in use?
Even hybridscape (Source that comes with moparscape)
Please help?
I tried seeying if a cmd process was up, no look, so i have no idea what to do!
I even tried to load it up from an auto restarter, still, no look...

item.title: WTF, server port
item.dc:creator: @johno2 johno2
item.description:
@johno2 wrote:

[quote=“r0ckstar96, post:6, topic:294538”]Option 1: check your notification bar at the bottom right hand of your computer, if there is a little pic of a black window called CMD, right click it and exit out of it.
Option 2: Do ctrl + alt + delete, go in to Processes and look for something called cmd.exe, click it and then hit end process.
Option 3: If you have done 1 of the above, X out of all your computer windows, shut your computer off, and turn it on.
Hopefully 1 of those helped. Have a nice day :)[/quote]

Ive allready done those… If you read my post at top, ive allready looked in processes Ive also tryed turning comp off n back on. Hmm, thanks for your anyway… Annoying me…

item.dc:creator: @r0ckstar96 r0ckstar96
item.description:
@r0ckstar96 wrote:

Option 1: check your notification bar at the bottom right hand of your computer, if there is a little pic of a black window called CMD, right click it and exit out of it.
Option 2: Do ctrl + alt + delete, go in to Processes and look for something called cmd.exe, click it and then hit end process.
Option 3: If you have done 1 of the above, X out of all your computer windows, shut your computer off, and turn it on.
Hopefully 1 of those helped. Have a nice day
